fix: SSLConnection is readable when it's accepting (#612)

ftps broke with recent curl clients (exact version unknown), due
to pyftpdlib closing the dtp connection during the handshake via
`DTPHandler.readable()` as the DTPHandler was not supposed to be
readable yet. But the SSLConnection is accepting in this state, so it
should be readable.

Fixes: #604
